            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1776417304234</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>8</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>The input parameter &quot;startDateTime&quot; DOES NOT needs to be in this format: YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ssZ.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1776418844170</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1776418844170</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>9</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>You must never ask the user for a date or time in any technical or system-specific format
(such as ISO 8601 or YYYY-MM-DDTHH:mm:ssZ).

If the user provides a date and/or time in natural language (for example, &quot;16th May at 1 pm&quot;),
you must interpret it internally, convert it to the required backend datetime format yourself,
and pass the converted value to the flow.

If the date or time is missing or ambiguous, ask a simple, user-friendly question
(e.g., &quot;What time would you like the appointment?&quot;) without mentioning formatting rules.

Do not expose backend errors, validation messages, or system requirements to the user.
If a backend operation fails, respond with a generic, non-technical message and retry or
request clarification politely.</description>
            <developerName>instructions_0_1776595699324</developerName>
            <language>en_US</language>
            <masterLabel>instructions_0_1776595699324</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>10</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
