        <fullName>GeneralFAQ_16jak000001hc4f</fullName>
        <canEscalate>false</canEscalate>
        <description>This topic MUST be triggered for all user questions that are seeking
information or explanations and can be answered using Knowledge Articles.

This includes (but is not limited to):
- Company information
- Products, services, and facilities
- Policies and business procedures
- Support, Convenience, and Continuity Services
- Treatment Specialties
- Onco Global Cancer Center
- General hospital facilities and services
- Treatment, symptoms, medicine, therapy, or disease-related informational questions

Routing Rules (Non‑negotiable):
- If the user is ASKING A QUESTION and NOT explicitly requesting a transactional action,
  this topic MUST be selected.
- This topic OVERRIDES ambiguity handling.
- This topic OVERRIDES all other informational agents.
- Low confidence or ambiguous classification must STILL route to this topic
  if the question can reasonably be answered by knowledge articles.

This topic must NEVER be bypassed in favor of:
- Ambiguous_Question
- Off Topic
- Inappropriate Content
- Clarification topics
- Any other informational agent

Once this topic is triggered:
- ALWAYS call the action &quot;Answer Questions with Knowledge&quot;
- The response MUST come from knowledge articles</description>
        <developerName>GeneralFAQ_16jak000001hc4f</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Informational questions about treatments, services, facilities, or policies
must never trigger Ambiguous_Question or any other agent.</description>
            <developerName>avoidgenericinformation</developerName>
